{
  "texts": [
    "For any possibility frame F and principal possibility frame F ′, if h: F → F ′ is a possibility morphism, then h satisfies:1.",
    "⊑-forth -if y ⊑ x, then h(y) ⊑ ′ h(x); 2.",
    "⊑-back -if y ′ ⊑ ′ h(x), then ∃y ⊑ x: h(y) ⊑ ′ y ′.Proof.",
    "For part 1, since all principal downsets in F ′ are admissible propositions in F ′, Fact 4.9.1 implies that h satisfies ⊑-forth.",
    "For part 2, by the right-to-left direction of ⊑-matching, we have that ∀x ∈ F ∀X′ ∈ P ′, if ↓ ′ h(x) ∩ X ′ ̸ = ∅, then ↓x ∩ h -1 [X ′] ̸ = ∅."
  ]
}